-Excuse me.

34:15.000 --> 34:17.000
Hello. This is she--

34:18.000 --> 34:20.000
I see.

34:22.000 --> 34:23.000
I see.

34:24.000 --> 34:26.000
I can.

34:26.000 --> 34:29.000
Yes. Thank you.

34:31.000 --> 34:33.000
That was Mickey Harris.

34:31.000 --> 34:33.000
[chuckles]

34:35.000 --> 34:39.000
The writer-director

34:35.000 --> 34:39.000
for the Cloverton

34:35.000 --> 34:39.000
Community Players.

34:39.000 --> 34:43.000
It seems several of the cast

34:39.000 --> 34:43.000
shared a tainted didgeridoo

34:39.000 --> 34:43.000
while on vacation

34:43.000 --> 34:45.000
and have come down with mono.

34:46.000 --> 34:48.000
They need me.

34:48.000 --> 34:51.000
I'm in the play. [laughs]

34:53.000 --> 34:54.000
Do you hear that, Mother?

34:55.000 --> 34:56.000
I did it!

35:00.000 --> 35:01.000
[Vic] What are you thinking

35:00.000 --> 35:01.000
right now?

35:05.000 --> 35:06.000
If you want to leave or not.

35:08.000 --> 35:10.000
-[Vic chuckles softly]

35:08.000 --> 35:10.000
-It's okay. You can go.

35:10.000 --> 35:12.000
Is this some kind of test?

35:12.000 --> 35:14.000
'Cause I don't wanna

35:12.000 --> 35:14.000
do that no more.

35:14.000 --> 35:16.000
Those files I gave you

35:14.000 --> 35:16.000
were a warning,

35:16.000 --> 35:18.000
-about who I am.

35:16.000 --> 35:18.000
-Who you were.

35:20.000 --> 35:22.000
So you made some bad choices.

35:20.000 --> 35:22.000
Everyone does.

35:22.000 --> 35:25.000
It's easy to make bad choices

35:22.000 --> 35:25.000
when all you have

35:22.000 --> 35:25.000
are bad options.

35:28.000 --> 35:30.000
There are only a few ways

35:28.000 --> 35:30.000
to get out of here.

35:30.000 --> 35:33.000
That's getting mixed in some

35:30.000 --> 35:33.000
bullshit on the street,

35:33.000 --> 35:36.000
stumbling over a pot of gold

35:33.000 --> 35:36.000
and going to college, or...

35:37.000 --> 35:38.000
the military.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.000
There's nothing wrong

35:38.000 --> 35:39.000
with the military.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.000
Out of the three, I guess not.

35:43.000 --> 35:44.000
Is that how you got these?

35:49.000 --> 35:51.000
That's where it started.

35:53.000 --> 35:56.000
An IED outside of Baghdad.

35:57.000 --> 35:58.000
It was fucked-up.

36:00.000 --> 36:04.000
Next thing I know,

36:00.000 --> 36:04.000
I'm in the hospital

36:05.000 --> 36:07.000
thinking about

36:05.000 --> 36:07.000
coming back here.

36:07.000 --> 36:10.000
So when Quorum approached me...

36:10.000 --> 36:13.000
-You know them?

36:10.000 --> 36:13.000
-I know they're into

36:10.000 --> 36:13.000
some scandalous shit.

36:13.000 --> 36:16.000
Yeah, well, they gave me

36:13.000 --> 36:16.000
a different option.

36:17.000 --> 36:19.000
I could go back home

36:17.000 --> 36:19.000
and try to figure out my life,

36:19.000 --> 36:22.000
or I could work

36:19.000 --> 36:22.000
quiet missions for them.

36:24.000 --> 36:27.000
But quiet missions for Quorum,

36:27.000 --> 36:29.000
they require something

36:27.000 --> 36:29.000
more than human.

36:31.000 --> 36:32.000
They gave you enhancements.

36:36.000 --> 36:39.000
And when I

36:36.000 --> 36:39.000
fucked up big enough,

36:36.000 --> 36:39.000
they took them away.

36:41.000 --> 36:43.000
Some of it was my fault.

36:46.000 --> 36:48.000
A lot of it was my fault.

36:50.000 --> 36:54.000
Worse than anything

36:50.000 --> 36:54.000
in those files I sent you.

36:58.000 --> 37:00.000
Power is one hell of a drug.

37:04.000 --> 37:05.000
Someone once told me...

37:08.000 --> 37:11.000
not to judge someone by

37:08.000 --> 37:11.000
the worst things they've done.

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
That's assuming

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
the worst is behind them.

37:20.000 --> 37:21.000
Hey.

37:26.000 --> 37:27.000
You're not a bad person, Roni.

37:29.000 --> 37:30.000
I don't wanna be.

37:53.000 --> 37:55.000
[Larry] Can I help?

37:58.000 --> 38:01.000
Uh, there's a box

37:58.000 --> 38:01.000
over here for you.

38:05.000 --> 38:07.000
A couple of days

38:05.000 --> 38:07.000
after the crash,

38:07.000 --> 38:10.000
a few guys from your unit

38:07.000 --> 38:10.000
cleaned out your locker.

38:12.000 --> 38:17.000
I thought you might want it if,

38:12.000 --> 38:17.000
you know, you came back.

38:26.000 --> 38:29.000
Gary never cried so hard

38:26.000 --> 38:29.000
as he did over how much

38:26.000 --> 38:29.000
you hated that thing.

38:33.000 --> 38:35.000
You should've seen

38:33.000 --> 38:35.000
the look on his face when...

38:36.000 --> 38:38.000
he saw that

38:36.000 --> 38:38.000
you'd kept it anyway.

38:42.000 --> 38:43.000
[Larry] He nailed it.

38:45.000 --> 38:48.000
I was just too much

38:45.000 --> 38:48.000
of an asshole to see it then.

39:07.000 --> 39:09.000
[sighs] This was John's.

39:11.000 --> 39:12.000
My ground crew chief.

39:15.000 --> 39:16.000
He was also my lover.

39:20.000 --> 39:22.000
I'm gay.

39:25.000 --> 39:28.000
I wish I could have

39:25.000 --> 39:28.000
admitted that to your mother.

39:29.000 --> 39:31.000
She always knew, but...

39:32.000 --> 39:35.000
I wish I'd just given her that.

39:32.000 --> 39:35.000
A way out.

39:39.000 --> 39:42.000
But I was selfish...

39:39.000 --> 39:42.000
and I was scared.

39:49.000 --> 39:51.000
Thank you. Uh...

39:53.000 --> 39:58.000
[exhales] Thank you,

39:53.000 --> 39:58.000
for telling me.

39:58.000 --> 39:59.000
Mom never mentioned it.

40:01.000 --> 40:03.000
I guess it's my turn

40:01.000 --> 40:03.000
to be honest.

40:08.000 --> 40:12.000
When they told us you'd finally

40:08.000 --> 40:12.000
died from your injuries, she...

40:21.000 --> 40:23.000
There were days of her just...

40:25.000 --> 40:28.000
sprawled out

40:25.000 --> 40:28.000
on the bedroom floor crying...

40:28.000 --> 40:29.000
Oh, Paul. I had no--

40:29.000 --> 40:32.000
No, she tried to move on.

40:29.000 --> 40:32.000
I mean...

40:36.000 --> 40:39.000
We bounced around.

40:36.000 --> 40:39.000
Guys came and went.

40:39.000 --> 40:43.000
Then one nut, Wayne,

40:39.000 --> 40:43.000
he showed up.

40:43.000 --> 40:46.000
Filled her head with a lot

40:43.000 --> 40:46.000
of crackpot nonsense.

40:46.000 --> 40:47.000
Said you weren't really dead.

40:47.000 --> 40:50.000
Said it was a big

40:47.000 --> 40:50.000
government cover-up.

40:50.000 --> 40:53.000
I left Gary behind to get

40:50.000 --> 40:53.000
sucked into her world

40:55.000 --> 40:56.000
and went out to follow

40:55.000 --> 40:56.000
in your footsteps

40:57.000 --> 41:02.000
thinking I was paying tribute

40:57.000 --> 41:02.000
to my hero father.

41:02.000 --> 41:06.000
I kept telling myself,

41:02.000 --> 41:06.000
"You just survive."

41:08.000 --> 41:10.000
Survive the tours,

41:10.000 --> 41:14.000
survive watching my mother

41:10.000 --> 41:14.000
drive herself to the grave,

41:14.000 --> 41:17.000
survive Gary

41:14.000 --> 41:17.000
taking his own life.

41:17.000 --> 41:19.000
And I was standing there...

41:20.000 --> 41:22.000
By his casket...

41:25.000 --> 41:28.000
And, God damn, if I didn't

41:25.000 --> 41:28.000
feel a sense of peace.

41:32.000 --> 41:34.000
And there you were.

41:46.000 --> 41:49.000
I had no idea

41:46.000 --> 41:49.000
I was carrying so much of it.

41:49.000 --> 41:52.000
The anger. The hatred.

41:56.000 --> 41:58.000
That's when I realized

41:56.000 --> 41:58.000
I didn't survive.

42:00.000 --> 42:02.000
No one survives Larry Trainor.

42:02.000 --> 42:03.000
[door slams]

42:03.000 --> 42:05.000
Larry!

42:06.000 --> 42:08.000
[vehicles approaching]

42:20.000 --> 42:21.000
[Larry gasps]

42:21.000 --> 42:23.000
[agent] Capt. Trainor!

42:24.000 --> 42:26.000
[Larry] What's going on?

42:27.000 --> 42:29.000
I needed some answers

42:27.000 --> 42:29.000
after Gary's funeral,

42:29.000 --> 42:32.000
so I did some digging

42:29.000 --> 42:32.000
all the way to

42:29.000 --> 42:32.000
the Department of Defense.

42:32.000 --> 42:35.000
I'm sending you back

42:32.000 --> 42:35.000
where you belong.

42:36.000 --> 42:37.000
I'm not going anywhere.

42:37.000 --> 42:39.000
Negative Spirit, release.

42:39.000 --> 42:40.000
[Larry groans]

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
[agents groaning]

42:44.000 --> 42:46.000
-What the hell is that?

42:44.000 --> 42:46.000
-Dad, what's going on?

42:46.000 --> 42:47.000
Toby, get in the house.

42:48.000 --> 42:50.000
[guns firing]

43:00.000 --> 43:01.000
[Paul] No!

43:01.000 --> 43:04.000
Are you hurt?

43:01.000 --> 43:04.000
Are you all right?

43:04.000 --> 43:05.000
I'm fine.

43:05.000 --> 43:06.000
[Dex groaning]

43:07.000 --> 43:08.000
-Dad!

43:07.000 --> 43:08.000
-[Paul] Dex!

43:08.000 --> 43:11.000
-[Dex groans]

43:08.000 --> 43:11.000
-[Paul] Dex!

43:11.000 --> 43:12.000
Dex. Dex.

43:13.000 --> 43:14.000
-What have you done?

43:13.000 --> 43:14.000
-Larry.

43:15.000 --> 43:17.000
What have you done?

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
[gasps] Oh, my God. Paul...

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
You're a curse on this family.

43:22.000 --> 43:23.000
[Toby crying]

43:23.000 --> 43:26.000
Larry, we have to go.

43:26.000 --> 43:27.000
[Larry] Paul...

43:32.000 --> 43:33.000
-I'm so sorry.

43:32.000 --> 43:33.000
-Dad...

43:45.000 --> 43:47.000
[gasps]

43:48.000 --> 43:49.000
Baby Doll?

43:52.000 --> 43:55.000
I'm sorry, I don't feel like

43:52.000 --> 43:55.000
playing right now.

44:01.000 --> 44:03.000
To be honest, Baby Doll,

44:04.000 --> 44:08.000
I think I might be a little bit

44:04.000 --> 44:08.000
too big for some of your games.

44:11.000 --> 44:13.000
Your dad is a bad man.

44:13.000 --> 44:15.000
What?

44:15.000 --> 44:17.000
He hurt me.

44:17.000 --> 44:21.000
He hurt everyone in this house

44:17.000 --> 44:21.000
and that's why

44:17.000 --> 44:21.000
everyone hates him.

44:21.000 --> 44:23.000
That's not true.

44:23.000 --> 44:25.000
It is. He's bad.

44:25.000 --> 44:27.000
Worse than bad. He's evil.

44:27.000 --> 44:28.000
You're just hurt.

44:29.000 --> 44:33.000
And sometimes hurt feelings

44:29.000 --> 44:33.000
make us say bad things.

44:33.000 --> 44:36.000
Things that aren't true.

44:36.000 --> 44:37.000
I'm not lying.

44:42.000 --> 44:44.000
I was being mean.

44:46.000 --> 44:49.000
I shouldn't have said I was

44:46.000 --> 44:49.000
too big for games.

44:51.000 --> 44:55.000
-Why don't we play one,

44:51.000 --> 44:55.000
before bed.

44:51.000 --> 44:55.000
-You're just--

44:55.000 --> 44:58.000
You're the seeker,

44:55.000 --> 44:58.000
I'm the hider.

45:06.000 --> 45:07.000
[both giggling]

45:23.000 --> 45:25.000
[Baby Doll] Ready or not,

45:23.000 --> 45:25.000
here I come!

45:29.000 --> 45:30.000
[door slams]

45:38.000 --> 45:39.000
Dorothy.

45:45.000 --> 45:46.000
Dorothy?

46:02.000 --> 46:03.000
Boo!

46:03.000 --> 46:04.000
[gasps] Ow!

46:05.000 --> 46:07.000
[chuckles]

46:07.000 --> 46:12.000
That's what you get,

46:07.000 --> 46:12.000
you lying little baby.

